{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 📚 Build Mamba SSM from Scratch - Part 3: Selective State Spaces (The Mamba Innovation)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Colab Ready**: This notebook runs on Google Colab with GPU support!\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objectives**:\n",
    "1. Understand why basic SSMs are not selective\n",
    "2. Learn Mamba's selective SSM mechanism\n",
    "3. Implement input-dependent parameter projections\n",
    "4. Understand how selection enables content-based reasoning\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. The Problem: Static State Transitions\n",
    "\n",
    "In our basic SSM, the matrices $A$, $B$, $C$ are **fixed** after training:\n",
    "\n",
    "```python\n",
    "h_k = A_bar * h_{k-1} + B_bar * x_k\n",
    "y_k = C * h_k\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This means:\n",
    "- ❌ **Same** state dynamics for all inputs\n",
    "- ❌ **Same** input projection for all positions\n",
    "- ❌ **Same** output projection for all states\n",
    "- ❌ Cannot adapt to **content** - only position\n",
    "\n",
    "This is fundamentally **positional**, not **content-based**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. The Solution: Selective State Spaces\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.1 Mamba's Key Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "The Mamba paper (Gu & Dao, 2024) introduced **selective state spaces**:\n",
    "\n",
    "Make parameters **input-dependent**:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}\n",
    "B_k &= \\text{Linear}_B(x_k) \\\\\n",
    "C_k &= \\text{Linear}_C(x_k) \\\\\n",
    "\\Delta_k &= \\tau_\\Delta(\\text{Linear}_{Δ}(x_k))\n",
    "\\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $\\tau_\\Delta$ is a **softplus** activation (for positivity).\n",
    "\n",
    "Now the SSM can:\n",
    "- ✅ Selectively **ignore** certain inputs\n",
    "- ✅ Selectively **focus** on relevant context\n",
    "- ✅ Adapt **per token** - content-based reasoning!\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2 Why Selection Matters\n",
    "\n",
    "Consider a simple copy task:\n",
    "- Input: `ABCDEFGH` → Output: `ABCDEFGH`\n",
    "- The SSM needs to remember everything\n",
    "\n",
    "Consider a retrieval task:\n",
    "- Input: `The answer is [MASK]...` → Output: depends on context\n",
    "- The SSM needs to **selectively** attend to relevant information\n",
    "\n",
    "**Selective SSMs can learn to**:\n",
    "1. **Filter** noise (small $\\Delta$)\n",
    "2. **Focus** on key tokens (large $\\Delta$)\n",
    "3. **Carry** information across long distances when needed"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Mathematical Details\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1 Selective Parameter Projections\n",
    "\n",
    "For each input $x_k$, we compute:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}\n",
    "s_B(k) &= \\text{Linear}_B(x_k) \\quad \\text{(selective input projection)} \\\\\n",
    "s_C(k) &= \\text{Linear}_C(x_k) \\quad \\text{(selective output projection)} \\\\\n",
    "s_\\Delta(k) &= \\text{softplus}(\\text{Linear}_Δ(x_k)) \\quad \\text{(selective step size)}\n",
    "\\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.2 The Selective SSM\n",
    "\n",
    "The recurrence becomes:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{aligned}\n",
    "A_k &= \\exp(A \\cdot s_\\Delta(k)) \\\\\n",
    "B_k &= \\frac{\\exp(A \\cdot s_\\Delta(k)) - 1}{A} \\cdot s_B(k) \\\\\n",
    "h_k &= A_k \\odot h_{k-1} + B_k \\\\\n",
    "y_k &= s_C(k) \\cdot h_k\n",
    "\\end{aligned}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: All operations are **element-wise** for efficiency!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
<parameter name="execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# @title 🔧 Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.nn.functional as F\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "device = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\n",
    "print(f\"Using device: {device}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Implementing Selective SSM"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   <parameter name="execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# @title 🏗️ Selective SSM Implementation\n",
    "\n",
    "class SelectiveSSM(nn.Module):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Selective State Space Model - Mamba's Core Innovation\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Key difference from basic SSM:\n",
    "    - B, C, and Δ are computed PER TOKEN (input-dependent)\n",
    "    - This allows the model to selectively attend to inputs\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, d_model: int, d_state: int, dt_rank: str = 'auto'):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.d_model = d_model\n",
    "        self.d_state = d_state\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Determine dt_rank (rank for delta projection)\n",
    "        if dt_rank == 'auto':\n",
    "            dt_rank = min(d_model, 16)\n",
    "        self.dt_rank = dt_rank\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # A: The core state dynamics (not selective - shared across all inputs)\n",
    "        # We store as log of eigenvalues for stability\n",
    "        self.A_log = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(d_state))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # D: Skip connection (not selective)\n",
    "        self.D = nn.Parameter(torch.ones(d_state))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Input projection (for x -> B, Δ)\n",
    "        self.x_proj = nn.Linear(d_model, dt_rank + d_state * 2, bias=False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Output projection (from state to output)\n",
    "        self.out_proj = nn.Linear(d_state, d_model, bias=False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Initialize with default delta\n",
    "        self.dt_init = 'random'  # or 'constant'\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def _forward_ssm(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Forward pass through selective SSM.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Args:\n",
    "            x: (batch, seq_len, d_model)\n",
    "        Returns:\n",
    "            y: (batch, seq_len, d_model)\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        batch, seq_len, d_model = x.shape\n",
    "        d_state = self.d_state\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 1: Compute selective parameters from input\n",
    "        # x_proj gives us: [Δ, B, C] projections\n",
    "        x_encoded = self.x_proj(x)  # (batch, seq_len, dt_rank + 2*d_state)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Split into components\n",
    "        delta = x_encoded[:, :, :self.dt_rank]  # (batch, seq_len, dt_rank)\n",
    "        B = x_encoded[:, :, self.dt_rank:self.dt_rank + d_state]  # (batch, seq_len, d_state)\n",
    "        C = x_encoded[:, :, self.dt_rank + d_state:]  # (batch, seq_len, d_state)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 2: Compute Δ (step size) with softplus for positivity\n",
    "        # Learn an initial value for delta\n",
    "        delta = F.softplus(delta)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 3: Discretize A (using selective Δ)\n",
    "        # A_bar = exp(A * Δ)\n",
    "        A_bar = torch.exp(self.A_log.unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0) * delta.unsqueeze(-1))  # (batch, seq_len, d_state)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # B_bar = (exp(A*Δ) - 1) / A * B\n",
    "        # Using the discretization formula\n",
    "        disc_factor = (A_bar - 1) / torch.where(\n",
    "            torch.abs(self.A_log.unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0)) > 1e-6,\n",
    "            self.A_log.unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0),\n",
    "            1e-6\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        B_bar = disc_factor * B.unsqueeze(-1)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 4: Parallel scan (from previous notebook!)\n",
    "        # h_k = A_bar_k * h_{k-1} + B_bar_k\n",
    "        h = selective_parallel_scan(A_bar, B_bar)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Step 5: Compute output: y = C * h + D * x\n",
    "        y = torch.einsum('bld,bln->bdn', h, C)  # (batch, d_model, seq_len)\n",
    "        y = y.transpose(1, 2)  # (batch, seq_len, d_model)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Add skip connection\n",
    "        y = y + x * self.D.unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Final projection\n",
    "        y = self.out_proj(y)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return y\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Full forward pass\"\"\"\n",
    "        return self._forward_ssm(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def selective_parallel_scan(A_bar: torch.Tensor, B_bar: torch.Tensor):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Selective parallel scan for SSM.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    A_bar: (batch, seq_len, d_state)\n",
    "    B_bar: (batch, seq_len, d_state)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns: (batch, seq_len, d_state) - hidden states\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    batch, seq_len, d_state = A_bar.shape\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Pad to power of 2\n",
    "    n_padded = 1 << (seq_len - 1).bit_length()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Pad\n",
    "    A = torch.zeros(batch, d_state, n_padded, device=A_bar.device, dtype=A_bar.dtype)\n",
    "    B = torch.zeros(batch, d_state, n_padded, device=B_bar.device, dtype=B_bar.dtype)\n",
    "    A[:, :, :seq_len] = A_bar.transpose(1, 2)\n",
    "    B[:, :, :seq_len] = B_bar.transpose(1, 2)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Parallel scan\n",
    "    for stride in range(n_padded.bit_length() - 1):\n",
    "        step = 1 << stride\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Even positions\n",
    "        A_even = A[:, :, ::step*2]\n",
    "        B_even = B[:, :, ::step*2]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Odd positions (shifted)\n",
    "        A_odd = A[:, :, step::step*2]\n",
    "        B_odd = B[:, :, step::step*2]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Combine\n",
    "        A_comb = A_even * A_odd\n",
    "        B_comb = A_even * B_odd + B_even\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Update odd positions\n",
    "        A[:, :, step::step*2] = A_comb\n",
    "        B[:, :, step::step*2] = B_comb\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Extract result\n",
    "    return B[:, :, :seq_len].transpose(1, 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test\n",
    "print(\"Testing Selective SSM...\")\n",
    "ssm = SelectiveSSM(d_model=64, d_state=128).to(device)\n",
    "x = torch.randn(2, 32, 64).to(device)\n",
    "y = ssm(x)\n",
    "print(f\"Input shape: {x.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Output shape: {y.shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check gradients\n",
    "loss = y.sum()\n",
    "loss.backward()\n",
    "print(\"✅ Backpropagation works!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Understanding Selection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
<parameter name="execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# @title 🎨 Visualize Selective Behavior\n",
    "\n",
    "# Let's understand what the selective mechanism learns\n",
    "\n",
    "ssm = SelectiveSSM(d_model=4, d_state=32).to(device)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create different input patterns\n",
    "x_uniform = torch.randn(1, 50, 4).to(device)  # Random noise\n",
    "x_pulse = torch.zeros(1, 50, 4).to(device)\n",
    "x_pulse[0, 10, 0] = 5.0  # Strong pulse\n",
    "x_keyval = torch.zeros(1, 50, 4).to(device)\n",
    "x_keyval[0, 5, 0] = 1.0  # Key\n",
    "x_keyval[0, 30, 1] = 1.0  # Value\n",
    "\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    y_uniform = ssm(x_uniform)\n",
    "    y_pulse = ssm(x_pulse)\n",
    "    y_keyval = ssm(x_keyval)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Get the Δ values (step sizes)\n",
    "    x_enc = ssm.x_proj(x_keyval)\n",
    "    delta_keyval = F.softplus(x_enc[:, :, :ssm.dt_rank])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    B_keyval = x_enc[:, :, ssm.dt_rank:ssm.dt_rank + ssm.d_state]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Δ values at different positions (key-value pair):\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Position 5 (key): mean Δ = {delta_keyval[0, 5].mean().item():.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Position 30 (value): mean Δ = {delta_keyval[0, 30].mean().item():.4f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Position 40 (after): mean Δ = {delta_keyval[0, 40].mean().item():.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Input patterns\n",
    "axes[0, 0].imshow(x_keyval[0].T, aspect='auto', cmap='viridis')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_title('Input: Key-Value Pattern')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Position')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Channel')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Δ values\n",
    "axes[0, 1].imshow(delta_keyval[0].T, aspect='auto', cmap='viridis')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_title('Selective Δ (Step Size)')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_xlabel('Position')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Δ Rank')\n",
    "\n",
    "# B values\n",
    "axes[1, 0].imshow(B_keyval[0].T[:, :16], aspect='auto', cmap='viridis')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_title('Selective B (Input Projection)')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Position')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('State Dim (first 16)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Output\n",
    "axes[1, 1].plot(y_keyval[0, :, 0].cpu().numpy(), label='Channel 0')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].plot(y_keyval[0, :, 1].cpu().numpy(), label='Channel 1')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].axvline(x=5, color='g', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='Key')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].axvline(x=30, color='r', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='Value')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_title('SSM Output')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Position')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('selective_behavior.png', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Notice how Δ varies per position - this is selection in action!\")"
   ]
  },
